==English==
===Etymology===
from Latin from [[Roman calendar]] ''bis sextum'' [[second]] six. In leap years there were two sixths of March in the Roman calendar, thus the succession of days was ... 5 - 6 - 6* - 7 ...

===Noun===
'''bissextile'''
# having an extra day, literally having two sixths.

